author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: VIDEO: Watch missionaries Whip, watch them Nae Nae
text:
HOUMA, LA (WVUE) - Hallelujah for girls who just want to have fun.
These two missionaries from Our Mother of The Eucharist, in Houma, LA, know how to get down on the dance floor. Well, better than many of us.
Sister Lilla Lottinger was recently visiting dad when some fellow missionaries convinced her to dance as a tribute to her late mother, who was a vibrant dancer.
Enter Silento and his hit song 'Watch Me (Whip/Nae Nae).' The spirit takes control and the women dance to everyone's delight.
Watch them Whip. Watch them Nae Nae. Clearly, this isn't their first time performing.
The missionaries said they were just having some innocent fun.
And if you think something is wrong with this dance, Sister Lottinger wants you to remember First Corinthians Chapter 10 verse 31.
"Whether, then, you eat or drink (or dance) or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God."
